\";s:29:\"https://oceanwp.org/?p=624466\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1191:\"<p style=\"display: block; padding: 0 0 24px; margin: 0 !important;\"><a href=\"https://oceanwp.org/blog/how-to-translate-oceanwp-woocommerce-store/\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/how-to-translate-oceanwp-woocommerce-store.png\" width=\"1200\" height=\"700\" title=\"How to Translate Your OceanWP and WooCommerce Store (the Quick Way)\" alt=\"How to Translate Your OceanWP and WooCommerce Store (the Quick Way)\" style=\"width: 100%!important;\"></a></p><p style=\"padding: 0 26px !important; margin: 0 !important;\">Translating a website used to be time-consuming and expensive. But with a multilingual-ready theme like OceanWP and WPMLâs new Translate Everything mode, you can automatically translate your entire store in...<p style=\"margin: 0!important;padding: 26px 0 0!important;\"><a href=\"https://oceanwp.org/blog/how-to-translate-oceanwp-woocommerce-store/\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"display: inline-block; padding: 10px 30px; color: #ffffff; background-color: #13aff0; border-radius: 30px; font-size: 13px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 1.4; text-transform: uppercase; text-align: center; text-decoration: none; letter-spacing: 1px;\">Read More</a></p></p>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:14:\"Allison Rivers\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:10268:\"<p style=\"display: block; padding: 0 0 24px; margin: 0 !important;\"><a href=\"https://oceanwp.org/blog/how-to-translate-oceanwp-woocommerce-store/\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/how-to-translate-oceanwp-woocommerce-store.png\" width=\"1200\" height=\"700\" title=\"How to Translate Your OceanWP and WooCommerce Store (the Quick Way)\" alt=\"How to Translate Your OceanWP and WooCommerce Store (the Quick Way)\" style=\"width: 100%!important;\"></a></p><p style=\"padding: 0 26px !important; margin: 0 !important;\">\n<p>Translating a website used to be time-consuming and expensive. But with a multilingual-ready theme like OceanWP and WPMLâs new <strong>Translate Everything</strong> mode, you can automatically translate your entire store in a fraction of the time, even on the tightest budget.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>See how it all works in this tutorial video:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\n<p class=\"responsive-video-wrap clr\"><iframe title=\"How to translate your OceanWP website with WPML (The quick and easy way)\" width=\"1200\" height=\"675\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/GxyPFzK634Q?feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen></iframe></p>\n</div></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>Why You Should Translate Your WooCommerce Store</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Thanks to continuous improvements in automatic translation, translating your online store can be one of the easiest ways to grow your business.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Reach New Customers</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>We all know ranking highly in search results draws in more customers. When you translate your site, you make it possible to <a href=\"https://wpml.org/documentation/support/multilingual-seo/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">rank well in search results for multiple languages</a>. Without changing any of your products, conducting costly research, or increasing your ad spend, you can reach a whole new market.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Increase Sales</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Once a potential customer lands on your site and finds the products theyâre looking for, itâs important to make it easy to complete their purchase. Having a fully-translated checkout process reduces the chance of cart abandonment. More completed sales = more money in your bottom line.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Improve Trust</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>When customers find a company they can trust, they come back again and again. Providing services and products in a personâs native language demonstrates an interest and willingness to engage with them. Continuing to provide after-purchase support in the form of translated documentation can be the difference between a one-time purchaser and a lifelong customer and advocate.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>The Best Tools for Translating Your Online Store Easily and Affordably</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>To get your online store up and running as soon as possible, be sure to use tools that allow you to build and translate your store quickly and easily. When you build a WooCommerce store using WPML and OceanWP, you can rest assured that everything will work as it should. This is thanks to WPML and OceanWPâs commitment to ongoing compatibility.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>OceanWP &#8211; A Theme Thatâs Multilingual-Ready</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>If you want to translate your site, itâs important to use a multilingual-ready theme like OceanWP. Multilingual-ready means you can translate every part of the theme, from <a href=\"https://wpml.org/documentation/theme-compatibility/build-multilingual-wordpress-sites-using-oceanwp-theme-and-wpml/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">pages, menus, and widgets</a>, to the <a href=\"https://wpml.org/documentation/theme-compatibility/build-multilingual-wordpress-sites-using-oceanwp-theme-and-wpml/oceanwp-extensions-compatibility-wpml/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">many extensions you can use to customize your WooCommerce store</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large is-resized\"><img src=\"https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/1.translated-store-1024x576.png\" alt=\"translate woocommerce store\" class=\"wp-image-624468\" width=\"768\" height=\"432\" srcset=\"//oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/1.translated-store-1024x576.png 1024w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/1.translated-store-300x169.png 300w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/1.translated-store-768x432.png 768w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/1.translated-store-1536x864.png 1536w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/1.translated-store.png 1920w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px\" /><figcaption><em>A translated online store built with OceanWP</em></figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<h3>WPML &#8211; Translate Your Whole Site Automatically</h3>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://wpml.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">WPML</a> is the most popular WordPress plugin for multilingual sites, and for good reason! The new <strong>Translate Everything</strong> mode, introduced in their latest release, allows you to:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Automatically translate your entire site in minutes;</li><li>Review the automatic translations yourself or hire a reviewer to make sure they sound natural and accurate;</li><li>Effortlessly keep your siteâs translations up to date (they update automatically any time you edit your default content);</li><li>Choose from Google Translate, Microsoft Azure, or DeepL to power automatic translation;</li><li>Translate content created with page builders like Elementor.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large is-resized\"><img src=\"https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/2.translating-site-automatically-1024x576.png\" alt=\"translate woocommerce store\" class=\"wp-image-624469\" width=\"768\" height=\"432\" srcset=\"//oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/2.translating-site-automatically-1024x576.png 1024w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/2.translating-site-automatically-300x169.png 300w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/2.translating-site-automatically-768x432.png 768w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/2.translating-site-automatically-1536x864.png 1536w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/2.translating-site-automatically.png 1920w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px\" /><figcaption><em>Sit back and relax as WPML automatically translates your site</em></figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>Although automatic translation isnât completely free, WPML gets great discounts from automatic translation providers due to the high volume they translate every month. They then pass along those discounts directly to you. This means automatic translation is super affordable for even the most budget-conscious.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Plus, with WPML, your translations are saved to your own database, not another pluginâs cloud. You own your translations yourself.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>WooCommerce Multilingual &#8211; Translate Your Products and Add Multi-Currency Support</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>WooCommerce Multilingual is a free add-on plugin that comes with the purchase of a WPML Multilingual CMS or Agency account.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>It allows you to translate:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Products</li><li>Product attributes</li><li>Product variations</li><li>Cart and checkout pages</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>&#8230;and more.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large is-resized\"><img src=\"https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/3.translation-options-for-products-1024x575.png\" alt=\"translate woocommerce site\" class=\"wp-image-624470\" width=\"768\" height=\"431\" srcset=\"//oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/3.translation-options-for-products-1024x575.png 1024w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/3.translation-options-for-products-300x169.png 300w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/3.translation-options-for-products-768x432.png 768w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/3.translation-options-for-products-1536x863.png 1536w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/3.translation-options-for-products.png 1920w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px\" /><figcaption><em>Deciding how to translate products in WCMLâs setup wizard</em></figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>It also includes robust <a href=\"https://wpml.org/documentation/related-projects/woocommerce-multilingual/multi-currency-support-woocommerce/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">multi-currency features</a> so you can display different currencies based on language or location. Plus, you can set exchange rates, custom shipping rates, and configure different payment gateways per currency.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large is-resized\"><img src=\"https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/4.multi-currency-settings-1024x576.png\" alt=\"translate woocommerce store\" class=\"wp-image-624471\" width=\"768\" height=\"432\" srcset=\"//oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/4.multi-currency-settings-1024x576.png 1024w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/4.multi-currency-settings-300x169.png 300w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/4.multi-currency-settings-768x432.png 768w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/4.multi-currency-settings-1536x864.png 1536w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/4.multi-currency-settings.png 1920w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px\" /><figcaption><em>Setting different currencies per language</em></figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<h2>Get Started with WPML</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Start translating your WooCommerce store today with WPML and WooCommerce Multilingual. A <a href=\"https://wpml.org/purchase/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">WPML Multilingual CMS or Agency account</a> includes everything you need to translate your entire site automatically and get your multilingual business up and running!</p>\n<p style=\"margin: 0!important;padding: 26px 0 0!important;\"><a href=\"https://oceanwp.org/blog/how-to-translate-oceanwp-woocommerce-store/\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"display: inline-block; padding: 10px 30px; color: #ffffff; background-color: #13aff0; border-radius: 30px; font-size: 13px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 1.4; text-transform: uppercase; text-align: center; text-decoration: none; letter-spacing: 1px;\">Read More</a></p></p>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:73:\"https://oceanwp.org/blog/how-to-translate-oceanwp-woocommerce-store/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"8\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:8;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:78:\"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n\n\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:8:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:73:\"How to Create a Dynamic Appointment Website with OceanWP &amp; Crocoblock\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:93:\"https://oceanwp.org/blog/how-to-create-a-dynamic-appointment-website-with-oceanwp-crocoblock/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:102:\"https://oceanwp.org/blog/how-to-create-a-dynamic-appointment-website-with-oceanwp-crocoblock/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Wed, 12 Jan 2022 07:42:50 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"Tutorial\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"WordPress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29:\"https://oceanwp.org/?p=623861\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1242:\"<p style=\"display: block; padding: 0 0 24px; margin: 0 !important;\"><a href=\"https://oceanwp.org/blog/how-to-create-a-dynamic-appointment-website-with-oceanwp-crocoblock/\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/dynamic-appointment-website-oceanwp-crocoblock-1.jpg\" width=\"1200\" height=\"700\" title=\"How to Create a Dynamic Appointment Website with OceanWP &#038; Crocoblock\" alt=\"How to Create a Dynamic Appointment Website with OceanWP &#038; Crocoblock\" style=\"width: 100%!important;\"></a></p><p style=\"padding: 0 26px !important; margin: 0 !important;\">Are you looking to build a dynamic appointment booking website? For those who think itâs hard to deploy, thereâs good news â itâs not. Nowadays, you donât need developers, coders,...<p style=\"margin: 0!important;padding: 26px 0 0!important;\"><a href=\"https://oceanwp.org/blog/how-to-create-a-dynamic-appointment-website-with-oceanwp-crocoblock/\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"display: inline-block; padding: 10px 30px; color: #ffffff; background-color: #13aff0; border-radius: 30px; font-size: 13px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 1.4; text-transform: uppercase; text-align: center; text-decoration: none; letter-spacing: 1px;\">Read More</a></p></p>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:9:\"enclosure\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:3:{s:3:\"url\";s:96:\"https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/8-appointment-booking-plugin-setup-â-step-3.m4v\";s:6:\"length\";s:1:\"0\";s:4:\"type\";s:9:\"video/mp4\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:3:{s:3:\"url\";s:78:\"https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/15-frontend-form-submission.m4v\";s:6:\"length\";s:1:\"0\";s:4:\"type\";s:9:\"video/mp4\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"Lana Miro\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:26789:\"<p style=\"display: block; padding: 0 0 24px; margin: 0 !important;\"><a href=\"https://oceanwp.org/blog/how-to-create-a-dynamic-appointment-website-with-oceanwp-crocoblock/\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/dynamic-appointment-website-oceanwp-crocoblock-1.jpg\" width=\"1200\" height=\"700\" title=\"How to Create a Dynamic Appointment Website with OceanWP &#038; Crocoblock\" alt=\"How to Create a Dynamic Appointment Website with OceanWP &#038; Crocoblock\" style=\"width: 100%!important;\"></a></p><p style=\"padding: 0 26px !important; margin: 0 !important;\">\n<p>Are you looking to build a dynamic appointment booking website? For those who think itâs hard to deploy, thereâs good news â itâs not. Nowadays, you donât need developers, coders, and designers. You just need the right tools.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In this article, youâll find out what makes a good appointment website. Weâll take you through the whole site creation routine and hand out the tools weâve used. In the end, you will figure out how to create a booking system using just OceanWP and several <a href=\"https://crocoblock.com/?ref=3457\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Crocoblock</a> plugins.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>What Makes OceanWP &amp; Crocoblock Great Together</h2>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>Visual site-building</strong>. Since Gutenberg is a visual block editor, website developers can save time switching back and forth between the admin panel and the front-end. Itâll suffice to create a page structure in the editor and ensure the front-end version looks the same.&nbsp;&nbsp;</li><li><strong>Fewer external plugins</strong>. Forget about separate plugins for custom post types, forms, booking management, custom fields, etc. To get the appointment functionality up and running, youâll need two Crocoblock plugins only.&nbsp;</li><li><strong>No middlemen</strong>. It means that developers do not have to rely on designers. You can take a demo template by OceanWP, rework its layout as you like, and add Crocoblock dynamic functionality to it.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<h2>Appointment Website 101</h2>\n\n\n\n<h3><strong>What is an appointment booking website?</strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Appointment websites are service-providing platforms where itâs possible to book a particular time slot. Often, these websites offer pay-per-hour services.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h3><strong>What do appointment websites look like?</strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<p>They can be one-page business card websites, where it is possible to book a particular service from a single provider. On the flip side, appointment websites can house multiple providers. In that case, the website has dedicated Provider and Service single pages and catalogs.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3><strong>Is it difficult to create an appointment website?</strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Not anymore. These days, you can build a dynamic website from scratch using the right tools â a page builder you prefer, a theme provider, some dynamic content plugin, and the appointment booking core.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3><strong>What are the main appointment website elements?</strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<p>These would be a theme, custom post types, an appointment booking engine, booking forms, Provider pages, Service pages, catalog pages, and listings.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3><strong>Can I add multiple providers to the same website?</strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Why not? Several professionals can provide one service. Make sure to assign a provider to the service to avoid confusion at the stage of filling the booking form.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Appointment Website: Basic Preparations</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>We decided to omit the early-stage preps like getting a domain name and choosing a hosting provider. Instead, weâll focus on the essence. For those who want to delve into detail, thereâs a super informative video by Ferdy Korpershoek.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\n<p class=\"responsive-video-wrap clr\"><iframe title=\"Make An Appointment Booking Website Using JetAppointment\" width=\"1200\" height=\"675\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/JFwmE9T5Fmo?feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen></iframe></p>\n</div></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>Get Crocoblock plugins</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Crocoblock introduced its <a href=\"https://crocoblock.com/blog/crocoblock-launches-custom-subscription-plans/?ref=3457\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">updated pricing</a> six months ago. What makes it cool? Itâs the <strong>Custom subscription</strong> plan. Now, to create a workable appointment website, you wonât have to spend much. Go to the <a href=\"https://crocoblock.com/pricing/?ref=3457\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Crocoblock pricing</a> page, unfold the <strong>JetPlugins </strong>tab, and add the necessary plugins to the cart.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Youâll need <a href=\"https://crocoblock.com/plugins/jetengine-gutenberg/?ref=3457\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><strong>JetEngine</strong></a><strong> </strong>â a dynamic content plugin that allows creating Custom Post Types â and <a href=\"https://crocoblock.com/plugins/jetappointment/?ref=3457\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><strong>JetAppointment</strong></a><strong> </strong>â a service booking WordPress plugin.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized\"><a href=\"https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/1-Crocoblock-shopping-cart.png\"><img src=\"https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/1-Crocoblock-shopping-cart-1024x472.png\" alt=\"screenshot of jetengine and jetappointment plugins in the shopping cart, necessary for appointment website\" class=\"wp-image-623868\" width=\"768\" height=\"354\" srcset=\"//oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/1-Crocoblock-shopping-cart-1024x472.png 1024w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/1-Crocoblock-shopping-cart-300x138.png 300w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/1-Crocoblock-shopping-cart-768x354.png 768w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/1-Crocoblock-shopping-cart.png 1172w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Such a custom package will cost you $45/year for one website and $93/year for unlimited websites. Plus, youâll be getting plugin updates and quality support for one whole year. Upload these plugins to the WordPress dashboard and get them ready for further work.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Install the OceanWP theme and choose a website template</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>There are two ways to install the core theme â the traditional one and the Crocoblock way.</p>\n\n\n\n<h4>Installing the OceanWP theme the traditional way</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Go to <strong><em>Appearance &gt; Themes</em></strong> in the WordPress admin panel and press â<strong>Add New</strong>.â You can use the search bar to locate the theme. Once found, install OceanWP and activate it.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full is-resized\"><img src=\"https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/2-OceanWP-theme-in-the-popular-themes.png\" alt=\"Screenshot of installing the OceanWP theme for the appointment website\" class=\"wp-image-623867\" width=\"729\" height=\"381\" srcset=\"//oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/2-OceanWP-theme-in-the-popular-themes.png 972w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/2-OceanWP-theme-in-the-popular-themes-300x157.png 300w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/2-OceanWP-theme-in-the-popular-themes-768x401.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 729px) 100vw, 729px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h4>Installing the OceanWP theme the Crocoblock way</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Use the Crocoblock <a href=\"https://crocoblock.com/blog/magic-of-website-building-install-crocoblock-with-wizard/?ref=3457\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Installation Wizard</a>. It can be downloaded from the Crocoblock account and then used to install OceanWP.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\n<p class=\"responsive-video-wrap clr\"><iframe title=\"How to install Crocoblock |  Installation Wizard\" width=\"1200\" height=\"675\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/Eok2CflNQI8?start=49&#038;feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen></iframe></p>\n</div></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>To choose a demo template, go to <strong><em>Theme Panel &gt; Install Demos</em></strong> and pick the one you need. Weâll use the <a href=\"https://gym.oceanwp.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\"><strong>Gym </strong>demo template</a> today. Remember that a demo cannot work as intended if some of the <a href=\"https://oceanwp.org/extension/category/premium/\">premium extensions</a> are missing. You may want to get them first.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><a href=\"https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/3-gym-demo-template-installation.png\"><img width=\"596\" height=\"658\" src=\"https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/3-gym-demo-template-installation.png\" alt=\"OceanWP core and premium extensions in a Gym demo\" class=\"wp-image-623866\" srcset=\"//oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/3-gym-demo-template-installation.png 596w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/3-gym-demo-template-installation-272x300.png 272w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 596px) 100vw, 596px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>As soon as the demo template installation is completed, you are ready to build a dynamic appointment website.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Building a Custom Appointment Website</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Inside every appointment and event scheduling website, there are custom post types for <strong>Providers </strong>and <strong>Services</strong>, automated appointment booking core, calendar integration, and a booking form. These are essential elements, but you are at liberty to extend the list however you like.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Now, letâs put JetEngine and JetAppointment plugins to good use.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Custom Post Types creation</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Why do you need to create a CPT? They will help you organize the website posts â services to services, providers to providers. Afterward, these posts can be easily interrelated to let the website users book a particular service from those who provide it.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\n<p class=\"responsive-video-wrap clr\"><iframe title=\"How to use Gutenberg editor for Custom Post Types\" width=\"1200\" height=\"675\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/Ytyc4XXlEYc?feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen></iframe></p>\n</div></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Follow the <strong><em>JetEngine &gt; Post Types &gt; Add New</em></strong> pathway in the WordPress admin panel to create a CPT. Remember that you need two post types â one for Providers and one for Services. Since we are building a Gym website, the post types will be named <strong>Trainers </strong>and <strong>Workouts </strong>accordingly.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Add the necessary meta fields to both post types. For the <strong>Trainers CPT</strong>, these could be:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>photo;</li><li>short bio;</li><li>work experience;</li><li>achievements;</li><li>gallery;</li><li>contacts.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full is-resized\"><a href=\"https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/4-trainers-CPT-meta-fields.png\"><img src=\"https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/4-trainers-CPT-meta-fields.png\" alt=\"meta fields added to the trainers custom post type for the appointment website\" class=\"wp-image-623865\" width=\"687\" height=\"569\" srcset=\"//oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/4-trainers-CPT-meta-fields.png 916w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/4-trainers-CPT-meta-fields-300x249.png 300w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/4-trainers-CPT-meta-fields-768x636.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 687px) 100vw, 687px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>For the <strong>Workouts CPT</strong>, the meta fields can be as follows:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>gallery;</li><li>description;</li><li>maximum capacity;</li><li>equipment;</li><li>health benefits.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full is-resized\"><a href=\"https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/5-workouts-CPT-meta-fields.png\"><img src=\"https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/5-workouts-CPT-meta-fields.png\" alt=\"meta fields added to the workouts custom post type for an appointment website\" class=\"wp-image-623864\" width=\"684\" height=\"524\" srcset=\"//oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/5-workouts-CPT-meta-fields.png 912w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/5-workouts-CPT-meta-fields-300x230.png 300w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/5-workouts-CPT-meta-fields-768x588.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 684px) 100vw, 684px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-background\" style=\"background-color:#f9f9f9\"><strong>Quick tip</strong>: JetEngine has got a useful <a href=\"https://crocoblock.com/blog/jetengine-glossary-feature-explained/?ref=3457\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><strong>Glossary feature</strong></a>. It allows you to create a set of meta fields and use them as options for Custom Post Types.Â </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Next, add as many posts to the newly-created Post Types as necessary. To do so, mouse over the CPT name in the WordPress admin panel and then press â<strong>Add New</strong>.â</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Once done, you may proceed to configure the JetAppointment plugin.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>JetAppointment setup</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>It is not that difficult to set the appointment booking plugin by Crocoblock. All you have to do is run the Setup Wizard and complete four installation steps.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Go to <strong><em>Appointments &gt; Set Up</em></strong> in the admin panel. Youâll be taken to the <strong>JetPlugins Settings</strong> page, namely to the JetAppointmentâs <strong>Set Up</strong> tab. Click on the similarly named button to run the Wizard.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>Step 1</strong>. You need to pick the Services and Providers post types in the corresponding drop-down selects. Donât forget to enable the <strong>Add providers</strong> toggle; otherwise, the field wonât appear. Click â<strong>Next</strong>.â</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized\"><a href=\"https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/6-appointment-setup-step-1.png\"><img src=\"https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/6-appointment-setup-step-1-1024x542.png\" alt=\"screenshot of appointment booking plugin setup â step 1\" class=\"wp-image-623863\" width=\"768\" height=\"407\" srcset=\"//oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/6-appointment-setup-step-1-1024x542.png 1024w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/6-appointment-setup-step-1-300x159.png 300w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/6-appointment-setup-step-1-768x406.png 768w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/6-appointment-setup-step-1.png 1040w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>Step 2</strong>. Here, you can see the required database table columns. Continue the installation if you donât feel like adding more columns. Weâll add Phone and Comments.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized\"><a href=\"https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/7-appointment-setup-step-2.png\"><img src=\"https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/7-appointment-setup-step-2-1024x818.png\" alt=\"screenshot of appointment booking plugin setup â step 2\" class=\"wp-image-623876\" width=\"768\" height=\"614\" srcset=\"//oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/7-appointment-setup-step-2-1024x818.png 1024w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/7-appointment-setup-step-2-300x240.png 300w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/7-appointment-setup-step-2-768x613.png 768w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/7-appointment-setup-step-2.png 1032w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>Step 3</strong>. This step is dedicated to configuring the service and provider-specific details like duration, buffer time, days off, working hours, etc. For a detailed step overview, please check out this <a href=\"https://youtu.be/ykMb0LFcMIo?t=53\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">video tutorial</a>.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-video\"><video controls src=\"https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/8-appointment-booking-plugin-setup-â-step-3.m4v\"></video></figure>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>Step 4</strong>. Lastly, you can integrate <strong>WooCommerce </strong>and create two appointment booking forms. The available options include âJetEngine Formsâ and âJetFormBuilder.â The first is intended for Elementor, and the second is for Gutenberg.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized\"><a href=\"https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/9-appointment-setup-step-4.png\"><img src=\"https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/9-appointment-setup-step-4-1024x637.png\" alt=\"screenshot of an appointment booking plugin setup â step 4\" class=\"wp-image-623875\" width=\"768\" height=\"478\" srcset=\"//oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/9-appointment-setup-step-4-1024x637.png 1024w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/9-appointment-setup-step-4-300x187.png 300w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/9-appointment-setup-step-4-768x477.png 768w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/9-appointment-setup-step-4.png 1031w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Press the <strong>âFinishâ</strong> button to finalize the setup.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full is-resized\"><a href=\"https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/10-appointment-setup-completed.png\"><img src=\"https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/10-appointment-setup-completed.png\" alt=\"screenshot of the appointment setup final screen\" class=\"wp-image-623874\" width=\"758\" height=\"560\" srcset=\"//oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/10-appointment-setup-completed.png 1010w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/10-appointment-setup-completed-300x222.png 300w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/10-appointment-setup-completed-768x567.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 758px) 100vw, 758px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Before you edit the appointment booking forms, you need to interrelate the Providers and Services posts. Open a Providerâs post and find the <strong>Related Services </strong>tab in the left sidebar. Type three characters into that text area and pick the necessary service once the system suggests it.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized\"><a href=\"https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/11-add-workouts-to-trainer.png\"><img src=\"https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/11-add-workouts-to-trainer-1024x683.png\" alt=\"apply services to the provider post\" class=\"wp-image-623873\" width=\"768\" height=\"512\" srcset=\"//oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/11-add-workouts-to-trainer-1024x683.png 1024w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/11-add-workouts-to-trainer-300x200.png 300w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/11-add-workouts-to-trainer-768x512.png 768w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/11-add-workouts-to-trainer.png 1226w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Repeat the procedure as many times as there are dedicated Provider posts. Once done, you are ready to play around with the forms.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>JetFormBuilder and form addition to pages</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Whatâs excellent about Crocoblock products is that some are actually free. Take <a href=\"https://crocoblock.com/plugins/jetformbuilder/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">JetFormBuilder</a>. Itâs a WordPress form-building plugin allowing site developers to build dynamic forms in the Gutenberg page editor. You can download the plugin, activate it, and use it right away.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Go to <strong><em>JetFormBuilder &gt; Forms</em></strong>. The two generated forms will be there. Weâll have to edit them since we added two columns to the DB table during the appointment setup. Now, we need to add the necessary meta fields to the form and post-submit actions.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Click to edit the <strong>Static Page Booking Form</strong> and add the missing meta fields by drag-n-dropping the corresponding Gutenberg blocks. Weâll need two â a <strong>Text Field </strong>and a <strong>Textarea Field </strong>â to add the Phone and Comment fields.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized\"><a href=\"https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/12-form-editing-in-gutenberg.png\"><img src=\"https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/12-form-editing-in-gutenberg-1024x729.png\" alt=\"adding text field blocks to the appointment booking form\" class=\"wp-image-623872\" width=\"768\" height=\"547\" srcset=\"//oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/12-form-editing-in-gutenberg-1024x729.png 1024w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/12-form-editing-in-gutenberg-300x213.png 300w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/12-form-editing-in-gutenberg-768x546.png 768w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/12-form-editing-in-gutenberg.png 1130w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Next, you need to input these fields into the Post Submit Actions. To do so, press the <strong>JetForm </strong>tab, scroll down to the <strong>Post Submit Actions </strong>section, and click on the pencil icon below the action name. Youâll see a Post Submit Action editing window, where you are supposed to select the form fields where they belong.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized\"><a href=\"https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/13-post-submit-action-setup.png\"><img src=\"https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/13-post-submit-action-setup-1024x721.png\" alt=\"setting up the Insert Appointment post-submit action\" class=\"wp-image-623871\" width=\"768\" height=\"541\" srcset=\"//oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/13-post-submit-action-setup-1024x721.png 1024w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/13-post-submit-action-setup-300x211.png 300w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/13-post-submit-action-setup-768x541.png 768w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/13-post-submit-action-setup.png 1130w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Besides that, you can set up WooCommerce integration here, provided that youâve enabled it at Step 4. Once done, click the â<strong>Update</strong>â button.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-background\" style=\"background-color:#f9f9f9\"><strong>Quick tip</strong>. Feel free to add several <a href=\"https://jetformbuilder.com/features/post-submit-action-controls-overview/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Post Submit Actions</a> at once but ensure that their conditions do not contradict one another. In that case, the form submission will fail.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Once you finish customizing the Static Page Booking Form, update it and add it to the website page. Weâve created a dedicated <strong>All Workouts</strong> page, which shows a dynamic <a href=\"https://crocoblock.com/knowledge-base/articles/jetengine-how-to-create-a-listing-template-in-gutenberg/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">JetEngine Listing</a>. A booking form will look lovely under the grid.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Open the page where you wish to place the form, find the <strong>JetForm </strong>block in the left sidebar, drag and drop it to the desired area, and then pick the form youâve just edited in the <strong>Choose Form</strong> drop-down on the right sidebar.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized\"><a href=\"https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/14-jetform-addition-to-the-page.png\"><img src=\"https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/14-jetform-addition-to-the-page-1024x535.png\" alt=\"adding the appointment booking form to the Gutenberg page\" class=\"wp-image-623870\" width=\"768\" height=\"401\" srcset=\"//oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/14-jetform-addition-to-the-page-1024x535.png 1024w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/14-jetform-addition-to-the-page-300x157.png 300w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/14-jetform-addition-to-the-page-768x402.png 768w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/14-jetform-addition-to-the-page-1536x803.png 1536w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/14-jetform-addition-to-the-page.png 1572w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Update the page and see how it looks on the front end.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-video\"><video controls src=\"https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/15-frontend-form-submission.m4v\"></video></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Now, the most attentive readers are like, âHow come the form is styled-up?â. Thatâs because weâve thrown another plugin into the mix. Keep reading to find out which. <img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/14.0.0/72x72/1f642.png\" alt=\"ð\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Go back to the WordPress dashboard and open the <strong><em>Appointments &gt; Appointments</em></strong> pathway. There you have it â all appointments are sitting tight. You can view, edit, delete them, filter, and change their status here.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized\"><a href=\"https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/16-gym-appointments.png\"><img src=\"https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/16-gym-appointments-1024x522.png\" alt=\"all gym appointments in the list view\" class=\"wp-image-623869\" width=\"768\" height=\"392\" srcset=\"//oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/16-gym-appointments-1024x522.png 1024w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/16-gym-appointments-300x153.png 300w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/16-gym-appointments-768x392.png 768w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/16-gym-appointments.png 1380w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>As you can see, the appointment booking functionality is up and running. However, there are more things you can do to make the appointment scheduling website even more dynamic.</p>\n\n\n\n<p></p>\n<p style=\"margin: 0!important;padding: 26px 0 0!important;\"><a href=\"https://oceanwp.org/blog/how-to-create-a-dynamic-appointment-website-with-oceanwp-crocoblock/\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"display: inline-block; padding: 10px 30px; color: #ffffff; background-color: #13aff0; border-radius: 30px; font-size: 13px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 1.4; text-transform: uppercase; text-align: center; text-decoration: none; letter-spacing: 1px;\">Read More</a></p></p>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:98:\"https://oceanwp.org/blog/how-to-create-a-dynamic-appointment-website-with-oceanwp-crocoblock/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"8\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:9;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:76:\"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:62:\"Black Friday / Cyber Monday 2021: Best Deals for OceanWP Users\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:70:\"https:/